{
  "step1": "Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease two 9‑inch round cake pans with butter, then dust with flour, tapping out excess. In a large bowl whisk together 2 ½ cups all‑purpose flour, 2 ½ teaspoons baking powder, ½ teaspoon baking soda, and ½ teaspoon salt, and ensure the mixture is evenly combined thoroughly.",
  "step2": "In another bowl, beat 1 ½ cups granulated sugar and ¾ cup softened butter until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add 4 large eggs one at a time, mixing well after each. Stir in 2 teaspoons pure vanilla extract, then set aside to let flavors meld before mixing with dry.",
  "step3": "Gradually add the dry flour mixture to the butter‑sugar blend, alternating with 1 cup whole milk. Begin with flour, then milk, and repeat, ending with flour. Mix each addition just until incorporated, avoiding over‑mixing to keep the cake tender. This method preserves air bubbles, ensuring a light, fluffy crumb throughout.",
  "step4": "Divide batter evenly between the prepared pans, smoothing tops with a spatula. Tap pans lightly on the counter to release air pockets. Sprinkle ¼ cup chocolate chips over each surface for extra richness, then gently fold them into the batter with a swift motion, ensuring they are well distributed throughout.",
  "step5": "Place pans in the preheated oven on the middle rack. Bake for 30‑35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center emerges clean with only moist crumbs. Rotate pans halfway through baking for even browning, then remove from oven and cool on racks for ten minutes before frosting cakes.",
  "step6": "Run a thin knife around each cake’s edge to release it, then invert onto plates. Frost with a silky chocolate ganache: melt 200 g dark chocolate with 100 ml heavy cream, stir until glossy. Pipe ganache between layers, then drizzle over the top, garnish with shaved chocolate for added texture and appeal."
}
